# 🏗 What is IoC (Inversion of Control)?

IoC means that the control of object creation is transferred from the programmer to the Spring Framework.

Without Spring:

```java
Student student = new Student();
```

With Spring:

```text
Spring Container
        │
        ▼
Creates Object
        │
        ▼
Provides Object to Application
```

---

# 💉 What is Dependency Injection (DI)?

Dependency Injection is a design pattern where Spring injects required objects into another object.

Example:

```text
Car
 │
Engine
```

Instead of Car creating Engine, Spring provides the Engine object.

---

## Types of Dependency Injection

### Constructor Injection

```java
public class Student {

    private Course course;

    public Student(Course course){
        this.course = course;
    }

}
```

---

### Setter Injection

```java
public void setCourse(Course course){
    this.course = course;
}
```

