# 🫘 Spring Beans

A **Bean** is an object managed by the Spring IoC Container.

Example:

```java
@Component
public class Student {

}
```

Spring automatically creates and manages this object.

---

# ⚙ Bean Lifecycle

```text
Bean Created
      │
      ▼
Dependency Injection
      │
      ▼
Initialization
      │
      ▼
Bean Ready
      │
      ▼
Destroy
```

---

# 📚 Bean Scopes

| Scope       | Description                 |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| Singleton   | One object per container    |
| Prototype   | New object every request    |
| Request     | One object per HTTP request |
| Session     | One object per user session |
| Application | One object per application  |

---

# 🏷 Spring Annotations

## @Component

Marks a class as a Spring Bean.

```java
@Component
class Student {

}
```

---

## @Autowired

Automatically injects dependencies.

```java
@Autowired
private Student student;
```

---

## @Configuration

Indicates a configuration class.

```java
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

}
```

---

## @Bean

Defines a bean manually.

```java
@Bean
public Student student(){
    return new Student();
}
```

---

# 🌐 Spring Container

The Spring Container is responsible for:

* Creating Beans
* Managing Beans
* Injecting Dependencies
* Controlling Bean Lifecycle

There are two types:

## BeanFactory

* Basic Container
* Lightweight

## ApplicationContext

* Advanced Container
* Most commonly used

---

# 📊 BeanFactory vs ApplicationContext

| BeanFactory   | ApplicationContext |
| ------------- | ------------------ |
| Basic         | Advanced           |
| Lazy Loading  | Eager Loading      |
| Less Features | More Features      |

---

